parameters: --!? (What's going on? Why is a native of this planet here?)

(I don't know. To think they'd come all the way to the
spaceship's hangar!)

(What should we do? Should we try to communicate? But we
don't have permission from our home planet!)

You... You're kappa, aren't you!? Hey, you're kappa, right!?
Leave the cucumbers you stole and go away! Hey, you're
kappa, aren't you guys!?

(...Kappa? No, we are an exploration team from the planet
Katsupar.)

(We are searching for a dangerous creature that escaped to
the third planet of this solar system. Young primate girl of
this planet, have you seen it?)

This creature is classified as a danger level S pest--after
dying, it activates its cells in the stomach of the creature
that ate it, reviving and continuing to live within the body
of that creature. It has an incredible regenerative ability.
Have you seen it?)

Um, I have no idea what you're talking about... What should
I do... For now, it's dark, so I'll light a torch.
(Ah!? Stop that--! You must not use fire inside the base!)
Zzzzzzt! High heat detected! Releasing water for safety!
Kyaaahh! Water is spraying from the ceiling!?

(That's called a sprinkler! Rest assured, we explorers have
no intention of attacking the natives.)

Ugh! Attacking with water, you really are kappa, aren't
you!? Bad kappa need to be punished...!

(No good! She doesn't understand us! She's got a sharp
weapon too!? )

(What an incredibly battle-capable native! She's not someone
we can subdue with bare hands!)
I won't lose to kappa-like creatures! Now, behave yourself!
(Can't be helped! We'll attack with the laser gun!)
(~~~~!? She, she dodged it? The laser gun!? )

If I can see where you're aiming, I can predict where it'll
come from! I'm so mad now! Take this--!

(Please, no more... We don't want to fight anymore! We
surrender!)

That look on your face, you seem a bit remorseful, huh?
Fine. I'll forgive you. But leave this place quickly.

(Could it be... Did it malfunction because of the water from
the sprinkler earlier? There was too much of it.)

(What do we do!? This is a terrible accident! At this rate,
none of us will be able to return to our home planet!?)

Karin: "The kappa seem to be crying in sorrow. Could it be
that this large iron contraption has broken? And because of
that, they can't return to their homeland?"

(Ah, there's not enough electricity. This is a critical
situation...)

(Ugh... We can't even communicate. Are we doomed to die on
this alien planet without completing our mission?)

Karin: "...Can't be helped. This has something to do with
lightning, right? If that's the case, I'll use my [Lightning
Cutter]--"
--Karin aimed the Lightning Cutter at the contraption.

Karin: "Lightning Cutter, full power release--! Here
goes--!!"
(We did it! It miraculously got fixed!? )
(Now we can return to our mother star! We're saved!)

Karin: "Phew... It seems to have been fixed Now, ride this
kappa vehicle and live somewhere else. You mustn't come down
to the human settlements anymore, okay? Understand?"

(Indeed. It's a complex feeling being attacked out of
nowhere and then saved, but we are grateful, native
daughter.)

(...However, we have no choice but to do this to those who
have seen us without proper procedure. Sorry.)
--Karin screamed and fell after being hit by a ray gun!

(For now, we'll take your sample data. You seem to have
notable combat abilities for someone from this planet.)

Karin: "(Ugh... I was careless... Am I going to be eaten by
the kappa now? I'm not even a cucumber...)"

(Rest assured. We're only taking your physical data. After
that, we'll erase your memory, so you probably won't
remember anything--)

Karin: "Kyaaahh...! So strong...! What is that ray...!
(collapses)"
--Karin screamed and fell to the ground!

(...Phew, that was nerve-wracking, but it seems things have
been settled.)

(Despite her appearance, she was skilled. Her movements were
quick and she was extremely proficient with her weapon... A
fearsome enemy.)

(...What do we do? Now that she has seen our true form,
should we revise our plans and return to our mother star
once?)

(We thought this was a primitive civilization without
electricity, but the natives are more combative than
expected. Our exploration weapons are insufficient. We need
more armaments for battle.)

(We wanted to make friendly contact with the inhabitants.
What shall we do with this native daughter?)

(...There's something about this young girl. Let's take her
as a sample. She should make a fine souvenir when we return
to our mother star.)
--Karin was placed inside a water container.

(We've altered her memories, but we can't completely change
them. There's about a 5% chance that she might recall her
encounter with us due to some unforeseen event.)

(If she does remember, she might come back to this base.
Reluctantly, we must destroy this secret base and move the
spaceship to another location.)

(No objections. If we make contact with the natives of this
planet again, I hope we can do so more peacefully--)
...Huh? Why am I passed out in a place like this...?

(Hmm... I feel like I encountered some unknown creature...
but... strangely, I can't remember anything... Was I just
having a weird dream in broad daylight...?)
